Cactus Code Thorn EinsteinMaxwell_TwoPunctures
Author(s)    : based on EinsteinMaxwell_TwoPunctures / TwoPunctures
Maintainer(s):
Licence      : LGPLv2+
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Purpose

This thorn constructs binary black hole puncture initial data for vacuum
Einstein-Maxwell evolutions that use E^i, B^i, Psi and Phi directly, rather
than a vector potential.  It is intended to feed the EinsteinMaxwell evolution
thorn based on the Zilhao et al. Maxwell-cleaning formulation.

The initial electric and magnetic fields are initialized as Coulomb/Dirac
monopole-type conformal fields associated with the punctures and stored as
ProcaBase::Ei and ProcaBase::Bi.  The cleaning fields ProcaBase::Psi and
ProcaBase::Phi are initialized to zero.

Important limitation: for generic mixed electric/magnetic charge assignments,
E x B is nonzero and therefore the electromagnetic momentum density is nonzero.
This thorn retains the original Hamiltonian-solve TwoPunctures workflow and does
not solve a coupled momentum constraint with that electromagnetic source.
